cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SP, cs.NA, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with theoretical guarantees of L1 minimization for sparse signal recovery from noisy measurements, which is a common problem in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the role of regularization parameter and the sparsity level threshold, which are important topics in machine learning and optimization, suggesting cs.LG (Machine Learning) as another likely category. The paper derives non-asymptotic bounds on sparsity level and signal-to-noise ratio, which involves mathematical analysis and optimization, indicating cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as a possible category. Finally, the paper provides explicit constants and numerical experiments, which are related to computational aspects and implementation, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a potential category as well.
